# ================================================================
#  PEERCITE PUBLISHERS — Netlify _redirects
#  Rules are evaluated TOP → BOTTOM. First match wins.
#  All rules use status 200 (rewrite: URL stays clean in browser)
# ================================================================


# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. STATIC PAGE CLEAN URLS  (remove .html)
#    Must come before the catch-all fallback at the bottom.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
/about          /about.html         200
/publications   /publications.html  200
/contact        /contact.html       200
/authors        /authors.html       200
/inpress        /inpress.html       200


# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. PDF CLEAN URLS — /shortcode/article-id  →  actual PDF file
#    MUST appear BEFORE the journal page rules (more specific).
#
#    Pattern: /<shortcode>/:splat
#    Maps to: /assets/pdfs/<FOLDER>/<shortcode>-:splat.pdf
#
#    Article IDs in the data look like: v1-i1-a1, v2-sp, etc.
#    Clean URL example: /pjmh/v1-i1-a1
# ----------------------------------------------------------------

